#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .claude/.env.template .claude/.env
#
# 2. FIRST USE PROMPT:
#    When you run Claude Code for the first time, it will detect available
#    MCP servers and prompt you to set them up. Follow these steps:
#
#    a) Review the MCP server sections above (sections 1-10)
#    b) For each server you want to use:
#       - Gather required credentials from the provider
#       - Set environment variables in .env file
#       - Confirm activation when prompted
#
# 3. Edit .env with your actual values:
#    - Add your API keys (required services)
#    - Update paths if different (OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH, etc.)
#    - Keep default values for optional services
#
# 4. Add .env to .gitignore:
#    echo ".claude/.env" >> .gitignore
#    echo ".claude/.env.local" >> .gitignore
#
# 5. Verify configuration:
#    - Test LLM connections: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY
#    - Test GitHub: GITHUB_TOKEN
#    - Test MongoDB: MONGODB_URI
#    - Test Atlassian: ATLASSIAN_EMAIL, ATLASSIAN_API_TOKEN
#    - Test Docker Hub: DOCKER_HUB_USERNAME, DOCKER_HUB_TOKEN
#    - Test Search: BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY
#    - Test Chrome: CHROMIUM_BINARY_PATH or CHROME_EXECUTABLE_PATH
#
# ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC FILES:
#
# You can create environment-specific overrides:
#
# - .env.local          : Machine-specific overrides (not synced)
# - .env.production     : Production deployment values
# - .env.staging        : Staging deployment values
# - .env.development    : Development machine values
#
# Load them with: export $(grep -v '^#' .env.production | xargs)
#
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:
#
# 1. Never commit .env files to version control
# 2. Rotate API keys regularly (monthly recommended)
# 3. Use different keys for dev/staging/production
# 4. Store secrets in: environment variables, K8s secrets, or vault
# 5. Log all secret access for audit trails
# 6. Use short-lived tokens when possible
# 7. Restrict token permissions to minimum needed scope
# 8. Use separate tokens for each MCP server where possible
# 9. Regenerate tokens if compromised
# 10. Store this file with restricted permissions (chmod 600)
#
# LOADING ENVIRONMENT:
#
# # In bash/shell:
# export $(grep -v '^#' .claude/.env | xargs)
#
# # In Docker:
# docker run --env-file .claude/.env image-name
#
# # In Docker Compose:
# env_file:
#   - .claude/.env
#
# # In Kubernetes (via ConfigMap):
# kubectl create configmap claude-env --from-env-file=.claude/.env
#
# # In Node.js (with dotenv package):
# require('dotenv').config({ path: './.claude/.env' });
#
